Comments_List:
 This course will introduce you to the wonderful world of French cinema and its evolution throughout the 20th century. The professor, Dudley Andrew, is a brilliant, kind-hearted man who is passionate about French movies and about seeing his students succeed. The seminar format is very conducive to excellent conversations about the movies, as are the discussions that take place after every Monday night screening. This class made me fall head over heels in love with French film. Thanks to this class, I will keep watching French movies long after I've left Yale.

I would recommend that in the future this course have a French-language seminar section. I loved having a French language discussion after the Monday night film screenings; 

I would also recommend that the film screenings be held on weekends; while I loved going to the screenings, they often conflicted with other meetings and practices that I had on Monday nights. Perhaps somehow the movies could be available online, in case a student has to miss a screening? That student could then do work to make up for their absence from the discussion.
